reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quest 3 UBS-C splitter, providing Midi and Power at the same time
reviews.reviewText: I use a Meta Quest 3 with a Piano training app to learn to play the Piano. I have an older midi keyboard that plugs into the headset using a UBB-C to Midi Cable. However the battery life on the Quest 3 is not good and I normally have an external battery pack plugged. reviews.reviewText: Got this to be able to use my gimp single USB-C laptop with a Yubikey and still charge my phone.The Yubikey eventually worked after about a half hour of trying to get either the PC or the phone to see it.It wouldn't charge my Pixel 6 Pro at all. reviews.reviewText: Nicely made. Does not claim to work with Samsung android and it doesnt. The charger passes through ok. It even charges fast. The first bullet in ad says headphone. The second bullet says data. No data on Samsung Android.Update. Make that 5 stars. The only thing I really wanted was to charge while ethernet tethering. That works fine. Super-remote internet access all day every day.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not reversible, data port host-only
reviews.reviewText: The item sort of works but is a little bit janky to get working because it's not reversible. A very important thing to note is that the data port is a host-only port. This means that if you plugged this device into your phone you could use accessories such as a keyboard or a flash drive but you wouldn't be able to transfer files from a computer or use it for Apple CarPlay as in those situations the phone would be acting as the device and the computer would be the host. Basically data can only go into the connected device but not out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars It doesn't work
reviews.reviewText: One of the two USB-C connectors has a lightning bolt on it, and the other has the old USB symbol (kind of like a pitchfork). There was no documentation as to which is for audio use and which is for power. I plugged the male connector into my iPad and then connected a power cable and a headphones cable to the two female connectors. When I put the headphones on, I cannot hear any music. But when I start to remove the headphones from my head, I can hear the music coming out of the speakers. I tried swapping what I was connecting to the two female ports and I could hear the music while they were on my head "normally," but my iPad was not charging.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Transfer speeds throttle performance
reviews.reviewText: The main purpose for this is to run a SSD enclosure to a Android device. A direct connect doesn't give the SSD enclosure enough power [15 watts > x] so this cable allows the storage to become readable when using a fast charger. I did a transfer test. 32 MBps. Too slow. I was expecting 300 MBps. This is an M2 SSD by the way. At that limit, might as well be a USB thumbstick.

Ich verwende es mit dem Samsung Galaxy S24+ Smartphone und dem FiiO KA1 USB-C DAC Adapter. Es lässt sich mit dem Splitter gleichzeitig Musik hören und das Handy aufladen. Das Produkt wirkt gut verarbeitet und hochwertig. Praktisch für mich sind die USB-C-Anschlüsse, da ich so keinen USB-A-zu-C-Adapter nutzen muss. Das Handy scheint damit langsamer zu laden, aber das ist für mich nicht schlimm. Immerhin versorgt der Splitter bei angeschlossenem Ladegerät direkt auch das andere USB-Gerät mit Strom. Das konnte ich durch die LED am FiiO KA1 feststellen, die dann leuchtet, auch wenn der Splitter gar nicht am Handy steckt.
